1.2 Summerize function

library(dplyr)
data.complete %>%
    group_by(treated_f) %>%
    summarise(count = n(), mean(bmi), median(bmi)) %>%
    knitr::kable()

Treated 147 26.93751 26.500

2 Graphics

2.1 Bar chart

library(ggplot2)
data.complete %>%
    count(typeca_f) %>%
    ungroup() %>%
    mutate(pct = round(prop.table(n) * 100, 1)) %>%
    ggplot(aes(x = typeca_f, y = pct, fill = typeca_f)) + 
    geom_bar(stat = "identity", position = "dodge") +
    viridis::scale_fill_viridis(discrete = TRUE) +
    guides(fill = FALSE) +
    geom_text(aes(y = pct + 2,    # nudge above top of bar
                  label = paste0(pct, '%')),  # prettify
              position = position_dodge(width = .9), 
              size = 4) +
    labs(x = "Cancer types",
         y = "Percentage of subjects",
         title = "Bar chart of cancer types") +
    theme_bw()

2.2 Box plots

ggplot(data.complete, aes(x = typeca_f, y = bmi, fill = typeca_f)) +
    geom_boxplot() +
    geom_jitter(width = 0.1, height = 0, color = "orangered") +
    guides(fill = FALSE) + 
    labs(title = "Boxplots of BMI by cancer types",
         x = "", y = "BMI") + 
    coord_flip() +
    theme_bw()

2.3 Histograms

ggplot(data = data.complete, aes(x = bmi, fill = typeca_f)) + 
    geom_histogram(color = "white", bins = 20) + 
    labs(title = "Histograms of BMI by cancer types",
         x = "BMI") + 
    facet_wrap(~ typeca_f)

2.4 Density plots

2.4.1 Facet-wrap

ggplot(data.complete, aes(x= bmi, fill = typeca_f)) +
    geom_density() + 
    facet_wrap(~ typeca_f) + 
    viridis::scale_fill_viridis(discrete=T) + 
    guides(fill = "none") +
    labs(title = "Density plots of BMI by cancer types", x = "BMI", y = "Density")

2.4.2 None facet-wrap

ggplot(data.complete, aes(x= bmi, fill = typeca_f)) +
    geom_density(alpha=0.3) + 
    viridis::scale_fill_viridis(discrete=T) + 
    labs(title = "Density plots of BMI by cancer types", x = "BMI", y = "Density")

2.4.3 Ridges

ggplot(data.complete, aes(x = bmi, y = typeca_f, fill = typeca_f)) +
    ggridges::geom_density_ridges(scale = 0.9) +
    guides(fill = FALSE) + 
    labs(title = "Density ridges of BMI by cancer types", x = "BMI", y = "Cancer Types") +
    ggridges::theme_ridges()
